              "reference": "1 Peter 3:15-16",
              "theme": "Hope",
              "text": "But sanctify the Lord God in your hearts, and always be ready to give a defense to everyone who asks you a reason for the hope that is in you, with meekness and fear; having a good conscience, that when they defame you as evildoers, those who revile your good conduct in Christ may be ashamed."
            },
            {
              "label": "This week",
              "date": "7/12",
              "reference": "1 John 3:1-3",
              "theme": "Hope",
              "text": "Behold what manner of love the Father has bestowed on us, that we should be called children of God! Therefore the world does not know us, because it did not know Him. Beloved, now we are children of God; and it has not yet been revealed what we shall be, but we know that when He is revealed, we shall be like Him, for we shall see Him as He is. And everyone who has this hope in Him purifies himself, just as He is pure."
            },
            {
              "label": "Next week",
              "date": "7/19",
              "reference": "Romans 15:4",
              "theme": "Hope",
              "text": "For whatever things were written before were written for our learning, that we through the patience and comfort of the Scriptures might have hope."
            }
          ]
        }
